external_knowledge:
- 'Academic realm of pollsters' refers to pollsters of the 'Academic' organization type;
- 'Beacon of wisdom' refers to the pollster 'Politico/GWU/Battleground';
- 'Cast its light on the most scrutinized polls' refers to the polls that have been viewed the most;
- 'Dawn of the year 2020' refers to the date '2020-01-01';
- 'Curious minds' refers to users who have viewed the polls.

- "sowed the seeds of support" refers to the pollsters who recorded a high average percentage of support for Obama;
- "tending to more than 45% of the garden's blossoms" means the average Obama support percentage is greater than 45%;
- "watering the soil with their polls" refers to the number of polls conducted by the pollsters;
- "in the year 2012" specifies the time frame for the polls.

- "pollsters" refers to polling organizations;
- "users" refers to individuals who access the polls;
- "access_logs" track user interactions with polls;
- "historical_data" contains records of when polls were conducted.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT poll_id) AS total_polls_accessed
FROM access_logs
WHERE user_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "Gardeners" refer to users;
- "Garden" refers to organizations;
- "Tending to the plants" refers to accessing the polls;
- "Different types of plants" refers to distinct poll IDs.

sql:
SELECT organization_type, COUNT(pollster_id) AS num_pollsters
FROM pollsters
GROUP BY organization_type;
